        {
            "language": "markdown",
            "source": [
                "Datatypes"
            ],
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "language": "markdown",
            "source": [
                "🤔 \"In JavaScript, you don't need to specify a data type when declaring a variable. JavaScript automatically determines the data type based on the value assigned. Variable name and data type are not the same thing.\""
            ],
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "language": "typescript",
            "source": [
                "let age = 19;                    // Number (8 bytes)\r\n\r\nlet name = \"Prasanth\";           // String (2 bytes/char)\r\n\r\nlet isStudent = true;            // Boolean (1 byte)\r\n\r\nlet city;                        // Undefined (no value)\r\n\r\nlet marks = null;                // Null (empty value)\r\n\r\nlet id = 1234567890123456789n;   // BigInt (variable size)\r\n\r\nlet uniqueId = Symbol(\"id\");     // Symbol (unique value)\r\n\r\nconsole.log(age);\r\nconsole.log(name);\r\nconsole.log(isStudent);\r\nconsole.log(city);\r\nconsole.log(marks);\r\nconsole.log(id);\r\nconsole.log(uniqueId);"
            ],
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "language": "markdown",
            "source": [
                "Operators"
            ],
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "language": "markdown",
            "source": [
                "⭐ Learn First (Used in Most Programs)\r\nArithmetic Operators\r\n(+ , - , * , / , % , **)\r\n\r\nAssignment Operators\r\n(= , += , -= , *= , /= , %= , **=)\r\n\r\nComparison Operators\r\n(== , === , != , !== , > , < , >= , <=)\r\n\r\nLogical Operators\r\n(&& , || , !)\r\n\r\nIncrement/Decrement Operators\r\n(++ , --)\r\n\r\nTernary Operator\r\n(?:)\r\n\r\nType Operator\r\n(typeof)\r\n\r\n\r\n🔥 Learn Next (Commonly Used)\r\nString Operators\r\n(+ , +=)\r\n\r\nNullish Coalescing Operator\r\n(??)\r\n\r\nOptional Chaining Operator\r\n(?.)\r\n\r\nSpread Operator\r\n(...)\r\n\r\nRest Operator\r\n(...)\r\n\r\nDestructuring Assignment\r\n([ ] , { })\r\n\r\nin Operator\r\n(in)\r\n\r\nnew Operator\r\n(new)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n"
            ],
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "language": "javascript",
            "source": [
                "let a = 10;\r\nlet b = 5;\r\n\r\nconsole.log(a + b);  // 10 + 5 = 15\r\nconsole.log(a - b);  // 10 - 5 = 5\r\nconsole.log(a * b);  // 10 * 5 = 50\r\nconsole.log(a / b);  // 10 / 5 = 2\r\nconsole.log(a % b);  // 10 % 5 = 0\r\nconsole.log(a ** b); // 10^5 = 10x10x10x10x10 = 100000"
            ],
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "mime": "application/vnd.code.notebook.stdout",
                            "value": [
                                "15",
                                "",
                                ""
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "language": "javascript",
            "source": [
                "let x = 10;\r\n\r\nx += 5;  // x = 10 + 5\r\nconsole.log(x); // 15\r\n\r\nx -= 3;  // x = 15 - 3, x value is overridden by new value from previous line x=+5 so x=15 in this line\r\nconsole.log(x); // 12\r\n\r\nx *= 2;  // x = 12 * 2 , x value is overridden by new value from previous line x=-3 so x=12 in this line\r\nconsole.log(x); // 24\r\n\r\nx /= 4;  // x = 24 / 4\r\nconsole.log(x); // 6"
            ],
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "mime": "application/vnd.code.notebook.stdout",
                            "value": [
                                "15",
                                "12",
                                "24",
                                "",
                                ""
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "language": "javascript",
            "source": [
                "console.log(10 == \"10\");   // 10 equals 10 → true only checks for value not type, so it converts string \"10\" to number 10 and then compares, so true.\r\nconsole.log('Type of \"10\": ' + typeof \"10\");  // \"string\"\r\nconsole.log('Type of 10: ' + typeof 10);   // \"number\"\r\nconsole.log(10 === \"10\");  // small logic between == and ====, === checks for both value and type not only value like \"**10 === 10 → true**\"  but false if type is different like \"**10 === \"10\" → false**\".tip use === for comparison to avoid unexpected type coercion.\r\nconsole.log(10 != 5);      // 10 not equal 5 → true\r\nconsole.log(10 > 5);       // 10 greater than 5 → true\r\nconsole.log(10 < 5);       // 10 less than 5 → false\r\nconsole.log(10 >= 10);     // equal allowed → true\r\nconsole.log(10 <= 5);      // false"
            ],
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "mime": "application/vnd.code.notebook.stdout",
                            "value": [
                                "true",
                                "Type of \"10\": string",
                                "Type of 10: number",
                                "false",
                                "true",
                                "true",
                                "false",
                                "true",
                                "false",
                                "",
                                ""
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "language": "javascript",
            "source": [
                "console.log(true && true);    // true AND true = true\r\nconsole.log(true && false);   // true AND false = false\r\n\r\nconsole.log(true || false);   // one true exists = true\r\nconsole.log(false || false);  // no true = false\r\n\r\nconsole.log(!true);           // opposite of true = false"
            ],
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "mime": "application/vnd.code.notebook.stdout",
                            "value": [
                                "true",
                                "false",
                                "true",
                                "false",
                                "",
                                ""
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "language": "javascript",
            "source": [
                "let n = 10;\r\n\r\nn++; // n = 10 + 1\r\nconsole.log(n); // 11\r\n\r\nn--; // n = 11 - 1\r\nconsole.log(n); // 10"
            ],
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "mime": "application/vnd.code.notebook.stdout",
                            "value": [
